\[PROPOSED\] ORDER SHORTENING TIME
ON PLAINTIFF'S MOTION TO COMPEL DEFENDANT'S DEPOSITION;
FOR SANCTIONS; AND FOR LIMITED LEAVE

Ex Parte Hearing:
Date: Thursday, November 13, 2025
Time: 9:00 a.m.
Dept.: R12

Reservation No.: \[\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\]

The Court, having read and considered Plaintiff MICHAEL JAMES ROMERO's Ex Parte Application for Order Shortening Time on Plaintiff's Motion to Compel Defendant's Deposition; for Sanctions; and for Limited Leave, the supporting declarations and memorandum, and the papers and records on file, and good cause appearing, ORDERS as follows:

1.  GOOD CAUSE APPEARING, the Court GRANTS Plaintiff's Ex Parte Application for an Order Shortening Time.

2.  Plaintiff's Motion to Compel Defendant's Deposition; for Monetary Sanctions; and for Limited Post-Cutoff Leave (the "Motion") is specially set and ordered on shortened time for hearing on:

    Date: \_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_
    Time: \_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_
    Dept.: R12

    at the above-entitled Court located at 8303 Haven Avenue, Rancho Cucamonga, CA 91730.

3.  Service Deadlines.
    Plaintiff must serve the Motion, this Order, and all supporting papers on Defendant at the first reasonable opportunity and in any event no later than:

    Date: \_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_
    Time: \_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_

    Service may be accomplished by any method permitted by statute, including personal service, overnight delivery, or electronic service where authorized. Electronic service is authorized under California Rules of Court, rule 2.251, where the parties have consented or are otherwise required to accept electronic service.

4.  Opposition and Reply -- Timing and Page Limits.

    a. Any Opposition to the Motion must be filed and served no later than **five (5) court days prior to the hearing** on the Motion.

    b. Any Reply in support of the Motion must be filed and served no later than **two (2) court days prior to the hearing** on the Motion.

    c. The Opposition and Reply briefs shall each not exceed **15 pages**, exclusive of exhibits, absent further order of the Court, consistent with California Rules of Court, rule 3.1113.

5.  Remote Appearance.
    Appearance on the Ex Parte Application and on the hearing of the Motion may be in person or by remote means as permitted under California Rules of Court, rules 3.672 and 3.1207, and in accordance with Department R12's procedures, unless otherwise ordered by the Court.

6.  Scope of Ex Parte Relief.
    This Order Shortening Time addresses **scheduling only**. All issues on the merits---including whether to compel Defendant's attendance and testimony at deposition, to set a firm deposition date, to award monetary sanctions (including under Code of Civil Procedure section 2025.450), and to grant limited leave to complete deposition after the discovery cutoff (including under Code of Civil Procedure section 2024.050)---are **reserved** for determination at the hearing on the Motion.

7.  Notice and Proof of Service.
    Plaintiff shall give notice of this Order forthwith and shall serve this Order on Defendant no later than the next court day after entry, and shall file a proof of service.

8.  Compliance.
    Failure to comply with the deadlines set by this Order may result in the Court striking late-filed papers, continuing or vacating the hearing, or issuing other appropriate orders in the Court's discretion.

IT IS SO ORDERED.

Dated: \_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_

